<h1><a name="begin_content"></a>OIG Fugitive: Susan Bendigo</h1>


<p class="charge">Accused of billing Medi-Cal $17.1 million with co-conspirators, collecting $10 million</p>

<p>Susan Bendigo is a registered nurse who was Director of Nursing for a company that provided nurses for home health agencies.  Investigators say from May 2004 through May 2007, Bendigo, 39, sent unlicensed nurses to treat patients in Medi-Cal, California’s Medicaid program, even though she knew Medi-Cal required licensed nurses to perform this work.  </p>

<p>In this scheme, Bendigo, who was born in the Philippines, and her co-conspirators billed $17.1 million to Medi-Cal and collected $10 million – about half of which came from the claims she submitted for services she provided with unlicensed staff.</p>

